The MIT License is the most popular kind of Open Source license on npm.
It gives folks very broad permission to use, change, and share software.

To apply the MIT License to an npm package you wrote:

1. Set `license` to the string `"MIT"` in `package.json`.

   The string needs to be exact, so programs, not just people, npm can
   tell the package is licensed on standard MIT terms.

2. Add a `LICENSE` file to your package. Add `MIT License` and a
   copyright notice top of the `LICENSE` file, then paste the MIT
   License terms below.

Create a new npm package and apply The MIT License to it, or follow the
steps above for a package you've already written.

Then run `$title verify`.
